problemStatement:
Given the following traditional functions, rewrite each as an arrow function with the same behavior. Test them by calling with sample inputs.

```javascript
function add(a, b) {
  return a + b;
}

function square(x) {
  return x * x;
}

function greet(name) {
  return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}
```

After conversion, call each function with `add(3,4)`, `square(5)`, and `greet('Node')` and log the results.

solutionCode:
const add = (a, b) => a + b;
const square = x => x * x;
const greet = name => `Hello, ${name}!`;

console.log(add(3,4));
console.log(square(5));
console.log(greet('Node'));
